place.name: HAROLDSTON WEST
place.gazetteerText: HARROLDSTON (WEST), a parish in Haverfordwest district, Pembroke; on St. Bride's bay, 5½ miles W of Haverfordwest town and r. station. Post town, Haverfordwest. Acres, 1, 718. Real property, £1, 011. Pop., 149. Houses, 28. The property is divided among a few. The living is a vicarage in the diocese of St. Davids. Value, £123. Patron, Pembroke College, Oxford. The church is not very good. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
